This page is one of many describing EvaluationFeatures that may be useful when comparing monotone to other similar (and not-so-similar) VCS systems.

# Description

The VCS tools should be portable to run on many kinds of development platform.

# Supported

Monotone is implemented in C++, and compiles and runs on all sorts of different kinds of Unix systems and Windows.  It is packaged in a number of linux distribution and packaging systems, as well as NetBSD pkgsrc which itself supports a number of different systems: see BuildingViaPkgsrc.

